    aliases: ["Endor", "Forest Moon of Endor"],
    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.470",
    summary: "The Forest Moon of Endor is the second of nine moons orbiting the silver-banded gas giant the Ewoks call Tana. Its lighter-than-standard gravity and dense ecosystem support three native sentient species. The Ewoks — meter-high ursine omnivores living in enormous treetop villages — are primitive in technology but highly skilled engineers and cunning warriors, as a legion of Imperial troops learned at the Battle of Endor. The Yuzzum dwell on the plains and forest floor, known for their long legs, powerful vocals, and keen ears; some have pursued careers as singers, including the Max Rebo Band's Joh Yowza. The Gorax are vicious, semi-sentient giants — rare enough to be considered legends. Local space is plagued by hyperspace anomalies that have wrecked ships from Sanyassa, Zorbia, and distant ports, creating a persistent castaway population. Before the Battle of Endor, the Forest Moon was visited only by castaways, fugitives, and pilgrims; the Rebels briefly based Alliance forces here before the Death Star's destruction overhead. Nagai invaders subsequently chased the Rebels off, followed by traders, miners, and even tour groups — though Endor's remoteness kept sustained interest brief.",
    locations: "Bright Tree Village (primary Ewok treetop village near the Rebel base; site of the post-Endor celebration). The Rebel Base (temporary Alliance installation used during the Battle of Endor; subsequently abandoned). Gorax Lair (deep wilderness; extremely dangerous). The Great Forest (primary biome; enormous ancient trees; Ewok territory).",
    ofNote: "Site of the Battle of Endor (4 ABY) — the ground battle in which Ewok forces helped defeat the Imperial garrison while the Rebel fleet destroyed the second Death Star. The moon's remoteness makes it nearly impossible to find without local knowledge or Rebel charts. Hyperspace anomalies near the system are a genuine navigation hazard. The small seasonal trading post is the moon's only offworld connection fifteen years after the battle. Ewoks are friendly to the Alliance and hostile to the Empire; attitude toward strangers depends heavily on first impressions."
